items.text: Dirty place.
The fish soup is good
Many nice food here, look at the long ques and you won't go wrong~
Flavoured muffins at only $1 at 3rd level. Cheap & good :)
Batang fish  seafood soup at level 3 is super yummy!! The fried fish has a unique seasoning that is equally crispy yet soft. Soup is clear and flavourful
Nasi lemak at store 02-24 increase price. The green rice one
Singpost postal box on ground floor, next to taxi stand
Nasi Lemak Setiap Jay a #02-03. Better than Changi Village and Boon Lay. Cheap and nice!!!
3F beef soup/noodle rocks TTM!! ^_^
Yummy salads on level 2 which you don't have to spend a bomb to eat!

History: "Golden Shoe" was coined by URA fr shape of upside-down shoe/boot outlined by Shenton Way, Raffles Quay, Collyer Quay, Boat Quay, Synagogue St, Church St, Telok Ayer St, financial heart of SG
Favourite Teochew Kway Teow mee @ #02-38. Free tissue service if u sit ard his stall!!! :)
Had a lousy nasi lemak from 02-14. Chicken over fried. Rice is wet. Vegetables tasteless. Waste money.
Price for most items of good portion is $2.50!  Very yummy selection too ;) hope this market remains as it is to retain the authenticity.
Seng Lee economic curry rice cheap and good.
Almost always here for my breakfast meal, kway teow soup and coffee to start my day
Be patient for seats here. Allocate at least 15 mins to find a spot.
Yummy Nonya Peranakan at Level 3. Yummilious with the spice & ingredients used for individual dishes.
#03-14 Say Seng Noodles - I give it 5 stars. $3 $4 or $5, good taste n value. Must have!
The slice fish soup/noodles at 3rd level is pretty good.
Cheap eats in the city!
Always long queue
$2 cai fan is great value but a tad bland
Limited breakfast choices. Try fishball noodles #03-14, popiah #03-02, prata #02-02, Malay/Muslim food corner on 2/F, beancurd #02-13, fishball noodles #02-38, wantan mee #02-32, prawn noodles #02-34
Must try the cheap & good salad @ #03-33 The Salad Corner, range $4.90-$7.90. Salad base, topping of ur choice, sauces to pick
One of the cheapest place to have ur meal in raffles place area!
There are baby "xiao qiangs" crawling around my table when im lunching today. Yucks!
The Chicken Rice from Golden Nur is a MUST buy if u are here..
Wantan noodles!
Coffee lovers - Ask for "brewed coffee" @ Al- Bismi stall. Thumbs up!!
Try the Fried Rice shop @ the 3rd floor . . . My usual order is Salted Fish Fried Rice, Extra Prawn, Extra Egg. Together with the green chili . . . Yummy! :-)
The popiah is so good!
Looking for cheap and good local delights in the CBD district? Look no further 'cos Golden Shoe is the place to go!
Remember to bring more tissues to "chop" seats :)
There are 2 queues if u go up to level 3, queue for the Ah Liang hor fun and skip the fish soup
Nice and cheap food that you can find at raffles area~~~
Lunch time!
$2 cai fan great way to save money
美香 seafood food #03-06
Roti john at Al-Haniffa is heavenly
One of the most affordable food places found in the heart of singapore's CBD, this place is super crowded during lunch time. Big variety of hawker stalls that can satisfy most palates.
Variety of food here...gotta be here early on weekdays to get table
Taxi stand always can't get cab after 10pm!
The prata at Al-amin is superb. Its actually the curry though.
Nasi lemak without chicken and 4 food only cost 2sgd. Cheap and good.
Plenty of good food at reasonable prices.
Remember to bring tissues to "chop" seats!! :D
Vegetarian options: Popiah, specialty vegetarian, local desserts, fruits, salads, soups, kaya toast, century egg porridge, lontong, Malay kueh, beancurd, prata
3rd level sells very cheap economic rice.. 4 dishes at $2.30!!!!!
Order beef fried rice add black pepper beef! Super awesome but 7bux. A must try from #03-23
This is on my top ten list of hawker centres in Singapore. Full of stalls with long histories and delicious foods. It's also very cheap for food in the city centre.
DBS 2atm 5049 i858
Try the nasi briyani at golden nur! #02-02
3rd floor of food ctr, good food at cheaper prices.
Second floor Rui Ji fish soup is awesome. So is the BCM on 3rd floor next to salad corner. Oh and most stalls close by 3pm except for the chicken rice stall.
Poh Kee Kitchen #03-23, tasty fried rice
The Thai Milk Tea from second floor is AHMAZING. My colleagues said it tastes just like the one in Thailand!
Mee soto rocks!
Wanton mee from 02-21 is quite good
Nais lemak is gd!
The prawn noodle from liang seah st prawn noodle #02-21 sucks. $5 for few pieces of prawn and meat that taste like rubber!
Amazing chicken rice at Golden Nur
Nasi lemak rice very nice. Real coconut milk rice.
Say Seng Mee Poh #03-14 Open 7:30am to 2pm
Crispy chicken rice is really good
Good and cheap food
3rd floor vegetable rice auntie very rude ahhhhh
Try the ginger tea at stall Mohamed Kassim Sahabat
Must tries: salad corner, popiah, fried beehoon, fish soup w red signboard.
東風發 Hainanese Boneless Chicken Rice is a MUST try! Cheap cheap @ $2.50 [small], $3.50 [large]. Yummy!
Enjoying a bowl of Say Seng Mee Pok to kick start the day. Best!!!
Love the lor mee sold by old uncle & aunty on level 3! $2 one big bowl! Be prepared to queue!
Nice Japanese stall on 3rd  floor at food court price!
Try Taqueria - L3 #03-29: Being intense foodies, we had the privilege to try the most unique Taco experience bar none. Bite & texture of the shell makes it all; Pollo, Carne, Pescado, all superb!!
nice satay beehon.
eat the nasi lemak from stall #02-14. nice green rice with extremely tasty fried chicken! yum yum...
Remember to 'chop' seats with tissues! Make sure it dont fly off!
Try the See Leng Stall and their Stringbean or Eggplant in Red Spice Sauce!! Excellent.
Chinese rice K3 at 03-07 is very cheap and taste good. 2 meats 3 vegs for $3.50!
nice mask lemak from #02-23 worth trying
Pho kee stall good food tasty fried rice and noodles
#02-35 Curry Rice is the bomb. Get ready to queue during peak lunch hour.
The fish soup at Rui Ji Fish Porridge is the best ever fish soup! I have introduced it to so many friends n they all agree totally. The sliced fish is always fresh n big n they generous in portions.
